Automated claims processing and electronic submissions accelerate reimbursement processes, reducing errors and improving financial performance overall for healthcare professionals. Customized Analytics and Reporting The financial condition of a healthcare practice is essential for making strategic decisions. HMS USA provides detailed and specific reports and analytics, providing insights into the most critical performance indicators, revenue trends, and improvement areas. Healthcare professionals can make informed choices to improve the financial performance of their practices. Patient-Focused Methodology In recognition of the importance of customer happiness, HMS USA implements patient-friendly billing procedures. Transparent and clear communication regarding the billing process, simple statements, and prompt customer support all contribute to a positive experience for the patient. Responsive Customer Service HMS USA prides itself on providing exceptional customer service. Their billing specialists are always available to answer questions, resolve issues, or advice on improving billing processes. The company's commitment to prompt customer service allows for a seamless and productive partnership between healthcare professionals. In summation, HMS USA is a reliable partner in the health industry and offers a range of medical billing services specifically designed to boost revenue, decrease administrative burdens, and promote the financial viability of healthcare providers. Description: Hardly is a A career development platform.
Full Description: – YOUR ATTENTION SHOULD BE YOUR CHOICE – Our software helps you tame the chaos by controlling your information flow. Log in to your apps through Hardly’s software and with a couple of clicks you can customize the alerts you want to receive at any given time— by project, person, or priority level. You can finally concentrate on getting work done, with less stress. And then once you are done? We have all of those social and promotional pings waiting for you.  – WHY CHOOSE HARDLY?  –  Hardly recognizes that people are dynamic and needs change. One day, you may need some notifications and not want others. The next day, your needs may be the exact opposite. Distracting notifications aren't limited to shopping websites or social media. Sometimes, distractions can come from another client or a coworker. Our app allows you to easily adapt and hone in on your needs for that day, without fear of missing anything important.  — Need to mute a specific client's pings across 6 different apps for one day? One-click.  — Need to prioritize everything on one project but mute the others? One or two clicks.  — Want to mute everything except your mom? Cool. We'll let in your mom's social pings, her emails, her texts and hold everything else. "BACK UP, WHY DO I CARE?" 23 mins are lost for every distraction and that adds up to 5 weeks a year— poof! But turning off all notifications is a luxury for bosses and independent workers (aka, not a realistic option for most). Alert fatigue has been a frequently discussed issue in the healthcare and emergency worker industry, but no one has addressed alert fatigue for collaborative desk workers. And current focus apps don’t take into account people’s changing priorities and needs for work and life— they are all cold turkey. You either get all notifications or none.

Full Description: E-CONCIERGE 2.0 is our innovative solution aimed at modernizing the home services industry. It's an intelligent virtual assistant, designed to streamline the often complex and time-consuming processes in the home service sector, beginning with the appliance repair industry. Through an interactive and intuitive Q&A process, E-CONCIERGE 2.0 engages with users to understand their needs, determine the nature of their service request, and schedule an appropriate service appointment. This advanced version is envisaged to integrate AI capabilities to offer more than just streamlining scheduling and dispatching. E-CONCIERGE AI will be a game-changer in its ability to predict potential service issues before the technician arrives. Using the power of AI, it will process the collected information, anticipate the problem, and advise the technician on the necessary parts and procedures they might need. This predictive function will dramatically speed up service delivery by eliminating unnecessary guesswork. Beyond predictive troubleshooting, E-CONCIERGE AI will also offer AI-enhanced technical support, guiding technicians through complex tasks and providing real-time solutions, equipping them to solve issues more swiftly and accurately. Our mission is more than just improving efficiency; we aim to revolutionize the experience for both customers and service providers. We envision a future where home services are reliable, effective, and user-friendly, and we are eager to lead the way in this transformative journey.

Description: Delivering hybrid capital and operating solutions, Threadneedle Ventures was founded by private equity dealmaker and operator Ann Berry
Full Description: Delivering hybrid capital and operating solutions, Threadneedle Ventures was founded by 15-year veteran private equity dealmaker and seasoned operator Ann Berry. Threadneedle Ventures draws on her global, multi-industry network to provide investment platforms, public companies and private enterprises with unique, pragmatic growth solutions that span strategy design to fundraising execution, talent sourcing to business development. Beyond advising with integrity, Threadneedle Ventures invests capital in and alongside its clients. Prior to focusing on Threadneedle Ventures, Ann was Chief Investment Officer of Jimmy Kimmel’s media platform Wheelhouse where she provided dozens of technology & consumer companies with a combination of content-driven marketing solutions and growth equity.  Her team partnered with portfolio companies to design bespoke branding campaigns executed on by Wheelhouse’s TV production, digital content and entertainment marketing divisions. From 2017 to 2021 Ann was a Partner & Investment Committee member at Cornell Capital, the global private equity firm in New York and Hong Kong where she acquired companies in the consumer, insurance and business services sectors.   In 2019 through 2020, Ann simultaneously served as interim CEO of PureStar, moving to Las Vegas to lead the national hospitality services company through the COVID-19 crisis. During her CEO tenure, she executed on a significant operational revamping of the company, repositioning it for both revenue recovery and margin growth. Under Ann’s leadership, PureStar was recognized for its groundbreaking diversity throughout the company’s 30 North American industrial locations and 5,000-strong employee base.  Ann began her career as an M&A banker at Goldman Sachs in London in 2003 before investing for the firm in global LBOs as a principal through 2016. While in Europe, Ann’s transactions spanned the UK, Chile, Germany and Sweden. She joined Goldman Sachs’ merchant banking division in New York in 2008, providing its private equity portfolio companies with in-the-trenches operating and restructuring support through the Great Financial Crisis. Ann has deployed billions of dollars in the industrials, natural resources and consumer sectors through take-privates, LBOs and structured capital solutions.    Ann serves on the board of baseball star Alex Rodriguez’s public company SLAM Corporation. She is an advisor to Cornell Capital and Anchor Capital. Ann previously served on the boards of Interline Brands (sold to Home Depot), GCA Services (sold to ABM), PureStar and Fekkai Brands, among others. She is an advisor to non-profit We Are Moving The Needle, founded by GRAMMY winner Emily Lazar to advance women in the music industry.    A sought-after speaker and active public equities investor, Ann is a regular markets commentator on Bloomberg, CBS, CNBC, Fox Business and YahooFinance.  She has appeared on numerous podcasts to discuss her experiences as a business leader and CEO.   Born & raised in London, Ann graduated from Cambridge University with a Double First Class Honors BA in economics and as a Trinity College scholar. Ann moved to the US as a Kennedy Scholar to attend Harvard Business School, graduating as a Baker Scholar with an MBA with High Distinction.  HQ-ed in New York, Threadneedle Ventures operates across the US & UK.
